            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-08-03T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-08-03T14:00:00-05:00" n="603" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d603">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.24 FLC/7–2848: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-08-03T15:00:00-04:00">August 3, 1948—3 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1111. From Hyssong<note n="26" xml:id="d603fn26">Maj. Gen. Clyde L. Hyssong,
                        Foreign Liquidation Commissioner since July 31.</note> OFLC. Your 1375 dated
                    July 28<note n="27" xml:id="d603fn27">Not printed; it reported an informal
                        Chinese Foreign Office view that October 31 might be acceptable as the date
                        to terminate declarations (893.24–FLC/7–2848).</note> Department believes
                    that negotiations regarding termination date China Bulk Sale agreement should be
                    maintained at high diplomatic level. In view fact conferences still active here
                    between OFLC and services, request no commitments be made prior Luboshez’s
                    return Shanghai. [Hyssong.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Marshall</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
